00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:21.000
You may need new kids crafts ideas everyday for your kids school project.

00:00:22.500 --> 00:00:25.000
Today, I'll make a beautiful wall clock from a paper plate.

00:00:26.500 --> 00:00:28.500
Your kids can make it easily for their craft project.

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:40.000
You need a paper plate, red acrylic color, cardboard sheet, brown paper, red paper, black paper, scissors and glue to make this wall clock.

00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:45.500
Paint the rim of the paper plate with red acrylic color.

00:01:01.000 --> 00:01:05.000
Write the numbers on your wall clock with the help of marker pen.

00:01:15.000 --> 00:01:19.500
Make the hands of your wall clock from black paper and paste on the clock.

00:01:51.000 --> 00:01:53.500
Make the pendulum frame from cardboard sheet.

00:02:16.000 --> 00:02:19.000
Paste brown paper over it to give it an elegant look.

00:02:49.000 --> 00:02:51.000
Make a pendulum from cardboard sheet.

00:03:22.000 --> 00:03:24.000
Paste a piece of red paper over it.

00:04:10.000 --> 00:04:12.500
Paste this pendulum with the clock.

00:04:23.500 --> 00:04:26.000
Finally, paste the penulam frame at the bottom of the clock.

00:04:34.000 --> 00:04:35.500
Paste a strong thread at the back of the clock.

00:04:43.000 --> 00:04:44.000
Your beautiful wall clock is ready.

